Answer:

4
Complexity
Time: O(n²)
Space: O(1)
Approach 2: HashMap (Optimal)
Intuition

For every number num, the required partner can be:

num - k
or
num + k

If these values have already appeared, they form valid pairs.

Store the frequency of previously seen numbers in a HashMap.

Algorithm
Create a HashMap to store frequencies.
Traverse the array.
For current number:
Add frequency of (num - k) to answer.
Add frequency of (num + k) to answer.
Update frequency of current number.
Return total count.
Java
class Solution {
    public int countKDifference(int[] nums, int k) {

        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int count = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {

            count += map.getOrDefault(num - k, 0);
            count += map.getOrDefault(num + k, 0);

            map.put(num, map.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
        }

        return count;
    }
}
